---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout title="Control Base – Work">
  <section class="project-detail">
    <div class="project-detail__inner">
      <a href="/work" class="project-detail__back">← Back</a>

      <div class="project-detail__header">
        <div class="project-detail__thumb">
          <img src="/images/projects/control-base.webp" alt="Control Base" />
        </div>
        <div class="project-detail__intro">
          <h1 class="project-detail__title">Control Base</h1>
          <p class="project-detail__tagline">A neo fashion brand</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="project-detail__meta">
        <div class="project-detail__meta-item">
          <span class="project-detail__meta-label">Year</span>
          <span class="project-detail__meta-value">2021</span>
        </div>
        <div class="project-detail__meta-item">
          <span class="project-detail__meta-label">Industry</span>
          <span class="project-detail__meta-value">eCommerce</span>
        </div>
        <div class="project-detail__meta-item">
          <span class="project-detail__meta-label">Service</span>
          <span class="project-detail__meta-value">Ui/Ux Design/Shopify development</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="project-detail__content">
        <p>Control Base brand operates at the intersection of what they call "emotional architecture" and futuristic aesthetics. The designs explore the contrast between raw, human vulnerability and cold, precise, mechanical elements. Aesthetically, inspiration is drawn heavily from cyberpunk themes and gaming (like Death Stranding), creating pieces that are often described as "wearable metaphors." You'll frequently see sharp structures and metallic surfaces in their expressive jewelry and apparel.</p>
        <p>it's a modern, custom-themed Shopify storefront designed with a focus on responsive layout and dynamic e-commerce features. The brand emphasizes small-batch production, ethical sourcing, and timeless design rather than chasing fast fashion trends.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style lang="scss">
  .project-detail {
    padding: 4rem 2rem 6rem;

    &__inner {
      max-width: 50rem;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    &__back {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      font: 400 0.875rem / 1 font-family(fraktion);
      color: color(secondary);
      opacity: 0.6;
      text-decoration: none;
      transition: opacity 0.2s;

      &:hover {
        opacity: 1;
      }
    }

    &__header {
      margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    }

    &__thumb {
      width: 100%;
      max-height: 24rem;
      overflow: hidden;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;

      img {
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        object-fit: cover;
      }
    }

    &__title {
      margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
      font: 700 3.5rem / 0.9 font-family(bigger);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: color(secondary);
    }

    &__tagline {
      margin: 0;
      font: 200 1.25rem / 1.5 font-family(editorial);
      color: color(secondary);
      opacity: 0.7;
    }

    &__meta {
      display: flex;
      gap: 3rem;
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
      padding: 1.5rem 0;
      border-top: 1px solid color(secondary);
      border-bottom: 1px solid color(secondary);
    }

    &__meta-item {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.25rem;
    }

    &__meta-label {
      font: 700 0.7rem / 1 font-family(fraktion);
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: color(secondary);
      opacity: 0.5;
    }

    &__meta-value {
      font: 400 1rem / 1 font-family(fraktion);
      color: color(secondary);
    }

    &__content {
      p {
        font: 200 1.25rem / 1.7 font-family(editorial);
        color: color(secondary);
        margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
      }
    }
  }
</style>
